race.comment: Great race but hard to go past the honest mare REGAL TYCOON (8), who has still yet to miss the frame in 10 starts. Has just the one win but continued her honest run of minors when resuming with a good second this grade at Bendigo. Regular rider Jamie Mott aboard and off the low draw will take catching again. BILLIE BRONX (6) resumed from a long spell with a big win at Warrnambool when well fancied. Fitter and aided by the big claim and low draw again. Will give a sight. GRINZINGER SUN (2) was solid fresh, finishing fifth but only a length from the winner. Fitter and did win when last second-up. Drawn for a soft run and should be hitting the line hard. TAPO (4) is another overdue and wasn't far away latest. Well placed with the claim. Something for the Multiples: MAJESTICITY (3)
